  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subject meets criteria for a DSM-IV Major Depressive Episode, lasting more than 4
             weeks

          -  Total MADRS score â‰¥ 20

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of any DSM-IV psychotic disorder

          -  History of drug or alcohol abuse or dependence in the preceding 3 months

          -  High suicide risk

          -  Clinically defined neurological disorder or insult

          -  Metal in the cranium or skull defects

          -  Skin lesions on the scalp (e.g. cuts, abrasions, rashes) at the proposed electrode
             sites

          -  Pregnancy
